    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n\r\nThe Painter needs to paint another diagonal line! This time from the top right to the bottom left!\r\n- Write the `if` statements and ***nested*** `if` statements needed within the `paint_diagonal(color)` function definition. \r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\nsofia = Painter()\n\ndef move_while_can():\n  while sofia.can_move():\n    sofia.move()\n\ndef take_all_paint():\n  while sofia.is_on_bucket():\n    sofia.take_paint()\n\ndef turn_right():\n  sofia.turn_left()\n  sofia.turn_left()\n  sofia.turn_left()\n\ndef turn_around():\n  sofia.turn_left()\n  sofia.turn_left()\n\ndef paint_diagonal(color):\n  #ADD FIRST IF WITH ITS NESTED CONDITIONALS HERE\n\n\n\n  #ADD SECOND IF WITH ITS NESTED CONDITIONALS HERE\n        \n\nmove_while_can()\ntake_all_paint()\nturn_around()\npaint_diagonal(\"pink\")\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
